*16.Toulouse FC               34  9 10 15  34-49  37  [*1,*4]    Relegated
*17.AS Saint-Etienne          34  8 10 16  42-56  34  [*1]       Relegated
*18.RC Strasbourg             34  7  8 19  28-61  29  [*3]       Relegated
*
*[*1] Saint-Etienne had originally had 7 points deducted for using 
*     players with false documentation (Alex (Brazil) and Maxim 
*     Levitsky (Ukraine) playing as EU foreigners on false Portuguese 
*     and Greek passports, respectively); on appeal this was changed
*     to the award of their round 19 match vs Toulouse (won 1-0) as 
*     a 0-0 loss against them and a deduction of 3 more points.  In
*     third instance, the original ruling was however upheld, that is,
*     Saint-Etienne have 7 points deducted and the match versus
*     Toulouse is not awarded but counted as a 1-0 win for Saint-Etienne,
*     as they didn't use more non-EU players than allowed regardless
*     of false passports.
*     On May 17, with one round of matches left to play, an administrative
*     court in Lyon ruled to suspend the point deduction pending further
*     investigation; the FFF appealed the verdict; on May 23, a civil court in
*     Toulouse ruled that the round 19 match should be awarded to Toulouse;
*     Finally, the match was awarded a 0-0 win for Toulouse and the  
*     point deduction for Saint Etienne was revoked.
*[*2] Monaco had 2 points deducted for fielding Pablo Contreras (Chile)
*     on false documentation; on appeal this deduction was cancelled.
*[*3] the abandoned match from round 22, was first supposed to be replayed
*     without any penalties to either club apart from the stipulation it
*     should played behind closed doors; after the French referees decided
*     they would refuse to officiate the match, it was awarded as a 0-0
*     loss to both teams; on appeal, it was decided the match was to be
*     replayed after all, and Strasbourg were penalised 3 points for failing
*     to provide security; referees still refuse to officiate the replay.
*     The 3 point penalty was later revoked again.  Later (after the end of
*     the season, on May 30) the replayed match (which Metz won 1-0) was 
*     awarded a goalless victory to Strasbourg as Metz fielded 'keeper Mondrag贸n,
*     who was eligible at the time of the replay but would not have been so at
*     the time of the original fixture.  Finally, however, Metz' 1-0 victory
*     in the replay counted.
*[*4] encouraged by the original success of their appeal against the
*     result of their match vs St Etienne, Toulouse also claimed the 
*     points of their round 17 match (1-1 away at Metz) as Metz' Colombian 
*     goal keeper Mondrag贸n allegedly played on a false Greek passport, 
*     in spite of the fact that Metz did not use more non-EU players than
*     allowed regardless of Mondrag贸n's nationality.  This appeal was
*     unsuccessful.  Rennes first lost an appeal for the points of their 
*     2-2 draw in round 23 against Metz in which Mondrag贸n played, but
*     eventually the match was awarded 2-0 to Rennes.

*NB: ATAC (Troyes) were renamed ESTAC (ES Troyes Aube-Champagne)

